3
[div class=p 
	"This here is my Mega Man 6 run, version 3. It beats my old version by almost a minute and manages to look a lot smoother. The run could still be considered to be a bit boring, but that's mostly the game's fault, as it is quite simple and straightforward.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When creating the movie, my first priority was to make it a no-hit run. I think I could've saved some seconds had I taken damage in a few spots, but I honestly think not taking hits is a better idea. It makes the run look a lot more professional. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The previous version was based mostly on hunches, this one is based on calculations. I discovered that using the Jet is only useful if you are going to use the entire height of the flight. I also discovered things like that it is slower to use the Jet in the Knightman stage, and that using the Jet in the Flameman stage is a major slowdown.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"About BEAT:
	]b
	" 
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"BEAT is a bird that comes to help Mega Man if the 4 letters are collected from the 8 first stages. 4 of the 8 stages branch and have two bosses, and you must choose either one. I did not get the utterly useless BEAT in my movie, so I took the path that was faster in each stage. Yamatoman is the only BEAT route I take.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"The major improvements:
	]b
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" I changed the order of the robot masters, Flameman was done first this time. Not using the Jet saves me a lot of time in the Flameman stage. Thanks to Wodball for the idea.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" I make good use of the tricks listed under "Mega Man 6 tricks" on the 
		[a class=extlink href=http://bisqwit.iki.fi/nesvideos/RockmanTricks.html rel=nofollow 
			"RockmanTricks
		]a
		" page. All possible open ladders (not between two walls) are abused, a pit in the Blizzardman stage is avoided.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" F.Blast is used a lot more because of its effectiveness.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The Jet Adaptor is used a lot less because of its slowness.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" I manipulated the bosses as best I could. I was unable to manipulate some bosses, especially the second time around.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" An alternate route was taken in Dr. X stage 4. I have no idea what I was thinking when I did version 2.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Every single jump is at least near pixel-perfect.
		[br 
		]br
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" I avoided switching weapons/adaptors many times in the Yamatoman stage by utilizing a ladder trick so that I could kill an enemy without switching from Jet to Silver T.
		$LF
	]li
